Nvm, I looked at the other posts and this is Clone Wars I guess.

It is from the series "Star Wars Rebels". I highly recommend it if you can watch it (the only way to watch it is to buy it, it isn't streaming anywhere), it is incredible.
http://i.makeagif.com/media/10-19-2015/0UPHjM.gif

The Clone Wars is better.
It has Grievous.

Disagree, Clone wars had grievous, but they made him an absolute ninny.

Unless you mean the clone wars with this grievous.
http://media.moddb.com/images/groups/1/5/4477/Dooku_Vs_Grievous_by_krakenwarrior.gif

I saw Grievous in action in this show first and was amazed at how terrifying he was throughout the series. Got so hyped when I saw him in "episode 3" only to be heart broken when they made him a giant wimp :(

Every other form of Grievous that a show tried to make has been a huge disappointment.
-
# #makegrievousgreatagain

The only reason he was so weak is because his organs were crushed by Mace Windu right before heading off into space. You can see evidence of this in episode 3, even though they never explain it. You actually see it happen in clone wars, though.

YES, finally someone else who knows. People are always complaining about "why is general grievous such a wimp," yet don't get that his chest was literally crushed and that's why he coughs. If my chest was crushed by mace windu without him even being near me, OF COURSE i'd be scared. He can't repair his heart since it was from his original body.

Plus in the Clone Wars he does kill a jedi & some clone troopers when they invade his lair. 

And in episode 3 when he actually tried 1v1'ing obi-wan he also got r e  k t.

It's unfortunate that so many skipped seeing the show, since it was honestly better than any of episodes 1-3. Just because it's animated doesn't mean it's bad. 

That show is the reason that Grievous is my favorite Star Wars character.

Animated shows seem to achieve what a lot of live action movies cannot. They aren't as limited and can make characters like general grievous so good. 

Then again the only people who don't like grievous are haters :P

And I honestly hope that they add Ashoka into Rogue One. It is set in the perfect time period for her to appear. One can only hope.

Can vouch day an' night for this one.

Genndy Tartakovsky be th' man for epic works on this scale.

... Th' new _Samurai Jack,_ anyone?

The Clone Wars took a few seasons to really hit its stride. The first two seasons of Rebels are far better than the first two seasons of Clone Wars. This series took Vader, and made him even more badass. They really sell the dread that comes over everyone when in his presence. Even his name creates fear.
